  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (b536f51 2023-08-21T00:16:24.090951402Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nRunning the command\r\n`forge test -vw`\r\ncreates an infinite loop.\r\n\r\nExpected result is either:\r\nA) an error stating that the flag -vw does not exist\r\nB) run tests with 1 V of verbosity & enter watch-mode\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's a screenshot of infinite processes spawning after running `forge test -vw`\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/104332780/a16c77e2-9915-4f6c-be18-bb34b981b8ec)\r\n",
